Investigation of Prosecutor General’s Office said who ordered Gongadze's murder
The investigation of the Prosecutor General’s Office established that General Oleksiy Pukach received an order to kill Georgiy Gongadze from former Minister of Internal Affairs Oleksandr Kravchenko.
According to sources of Ukrainska Pravda, it is said in a resolution of investigator of the Prosecutor General’s Office Oleksandr Kharchenko on institution of criminal proceedings against O. Pukach.
The resolution was passed on September 7, 2010 and in accordance with it O. Pukach is charged under three articles of the Penal Code.